Patch Set 6:

Apologies, I'm a bit late to the game on this one...

Why doesn't this work the same as LCME_PREF_RW, which is also a "whole mirror" flag?

"/* The flags can be set by users at mirror creation time. */
#define LCME_USER_FLAGS         (LCME_FL_PREF_RW)

/* The flags are for mirrors */
#define LCME_MIRROR_FLAGS       (LCME_FL_NOSYNC)"

And why doesn't "                        if (last_mirror->m_flags & ~LCME_USER_FLAGS) {
                                fprintf(stderr,
                                        "%s: unsupported mirror flags: %s\n",
                                        progname, optarg);
                                result = -EINVAL;
                                goto error;
                        }"

prevent it from being set?  Clearly that's just in some scenarios, but it looks odd.
